pomProject.name: AutoComplete
pomProject.description: AutoComplete is a library allowing you to add IDE-like auto-completion (aka "code completion" or "Intellisense") to any Swing JTextComponent. Special integration is added for RSyntaxTextArea, since this feature is commonly needed when editing source code. Features include: Drop-down completion choice list.  Optional companion "description" window, complete with full HTML support and navigable with hyperlinks. Optional parameter completion assistance for functions and methods, ala Eclipse and NetBeans.  Completion information is typically specified in an XML file, but can even be dynamic.

pomProject.name: JOpt Simple
pomProject.description: A Java library for parsing command line options

pomProject.name: JSON in Java
pomProject.description: JSON is a light-weight, language independent, data interchange format. See http://www.JSON.org/ The files in this package implement JSON encoders/decoders in Java. It also includes the capability to convert between JSON and XML, HTTP headers, Cookies, and CDL. This is a reference implementation. There is a large number of JSON packages in Java. Perhaps someday the Java community will standardize on one. Until then, choose carefully. The license includes this restriction: "The software shall be used for good, not evil." If your conscience cannot live with that, then choose a different package.

pomProject.name: RSyntaxTextArea
pomProject.description: RSyntaxTextArea is the syntax highlighting text editor used in RText, pulled out into its own jar so it is easily usable in any application. Features include Syntax highlighting for 20+ languages, Code completion, Regex find and replace, Macros, Code templates, Unlimited undo/redo Line numbering and bracket matching.
